Feature: a spike executes via Workflow and returns its finding as markdown, not a large array-heavy StructuredOutput

  Lifecycle stages 3/4 execution + emit — ADR-032 D1/D2/D3, PDR-016 capability point 5.
  A spike runs via the Workflow multi-agent engine and returns its durable output as a
  markdown findings document (prose plus small tables). It does not emit a large,
  array-heavy StructuredOutput, which a heavy-context agent is known to hang on; any
  structured emit a spike does use must be small and flat with no big arrays. This is a
  reliability requirement, not a style note — it is the difference between a completed
  spike whose finding survives and one whose finding is lost in a hung emit. This is a
  LEAD-PROCESS behavior: Workflow is the lead host's execution engine, not a current BC,
  so there is no BC addressee; flagged for the discriminator as the scenario most
  BC-adjacent should a Workflow-owning BC ever exist.
  @scenario_hash:765f5473b2d121ec
  Scenario: a spike executes via Workflow and returns a markdown finding rather than a large array-heavy structured emit
    Given a spike that runs its execution through the Workflow multi-agent engine
    When the spike emits its durable finding
    Then the finding is returned as a markdown findings document of prose and small tables
    And the spike does not emit a large array-heavy StructuredOutput as its durable finding
    And any structured emit the spike does use is small and flat with no big arrays
